- [ ] TMUX session started (`tmux new -s [session_name]`)
- [ ] Logging started inside the session (`prefix + Shift-P` or `tmux capture-pane -pS -32768 > output.txt`)
- [ ] Session properly named per host/subdomain (`tmux rename-session [new_name]`)
- [ ] Major actions and commands being logged
- [ ] Splits/panes organized logically (optional)
- [ ] Start new session (`tmux new -s [name]`)
- [ ] List sessions (`tmux ls`)
- [ ] Attach to session (`tmux attach -t [name]`)
- [ ] Rename session (`tmux rename-session -t [old-name] [new-name]`)
- [ ] Detach session (`Ctrl-b d`)
- [ ] Vertical split (`Ctrl-b %`)
- [ ] Horizontal split (`Ctrl-b "`)
- [ ] Move between panes (`Ctrl-b` + arrow key)
- [ ] Close a pane (`Ctrl-b x`)
- [ ] Start/stop logging (`prefix + Shift-P`)
- [ ] Manual capture output (`tmux capture-pane -pS -32768 > [filename].txt`)


## ðŸ›  Quick TMUX Commands Refresher:

-  Start new session: `tmux new -s [name]`
    
-  List sessions: `tmux ls`
    
-  Attach to session: `tmux attach -t [name]`
    
-  Rename session: `tmux rename-session -t [old-name] [new-name]`
    
-  Detach session: `Ctrl-b d`
    
-  Vertical split: `Ctrl-b %`
    
-  Horizontal split: `Ctrl-b "`
    
-  Move between panes: `Ctrl-b` + arrow key
    
-  Close a pane: `Ctrl-b x`
    
-  Start/stop logging (with plugin): `prefix + Shift-P`
    
-  Manual capture output: `tmux capture-pane -pS -32768 > [filename].txt`
